# Components (UI layer)

Cross-check `project-spec.md` §5–6 and `streamlite-project.mdc` (screens do not fetch data).

## Placement

- Put **reusable** UI in `src/components/**` — not under `src/screens/`.
- Organise by feature area (`common/`, `home/`, etc.) per project structure.

## Purity and hooks

- Keep components **UI-focused**: **no data fetching** (`useEffect` + API) and **no navigation** calls — those belong in screens or thin containers. Passing props from parents is preferred.
- **Zustand** (e.g. watchlist) may be used in small interactive components when it matches existing patterns — avoid duplicating hook/store logic that already exists upstream.
- **Never** call hooks conditionally (follow Rules of Hooks).

## Reusable component API

- Accept optional **`style`** (or `contentStyle` / nested style props) and **merge** with defaults so callers can override layout without forking components.
- Accept **`testID`** on root touchables and forward it for tests.

## Composition

- Prefer **composition** over inheritance; use **`children`** for flexible slots.
- Avoid **monolithic** files: split into subcomponents (e.g. header / content / footer) when a file approaches **~150–200 lines** or multiple responsibilities.
- **Do not duplicate** UI — extract shared primitives (buttons, rows, cards) used in more than one place.

## Lists

- For **long or virtualised** lists, prefer **`FlatList`** (or `FlashList` if added) over mapping inside `ScrollView`. Short horizontal carousels may use `ScrollView` per screen spec.
